Instructions to run:
- Save all files in the same folder.
- Open index.html in a modern browser.
- Use the keyboard controls listed in the sidebar, or the buttons to start/pause/restart.

Enjoy playing Tetris!

[2025-16-09 22:33:37 INFO] **[Seminar Conclusion]**:

 Below is the architecture plan followed by the complete, functional code for a browser-based Tetris game implemented in vanilla JavaScript with a canvas-based GUI.

Core components and responsibilities:
- index.html: Main HTML entry; sets up the page, canvases, and UI elements.
- style.css: Styles for layout and visuals.
- main.js: Bootstraps the game, wiring up UI controls and creating the Game instance.
- utils.js:
  - shuffleArray(arr): Utility to shuffle arrays (used for 7-bag randomizer).
  - clamp(value, min, max): Utility clamp function.
- shapes.js:
  - SHAPES: Definitions of all seven tetromino rotations.
  - COLORS: Color mapping for tetromino types.
  - SPAWN_OFFSETS: Optional spawn offset per piece for nicer centering.
- board.js:
  - Board class: Manages grid, collision detection, merging pieces, line clearing.
- piece.js:
  - Piece class: Encapsulates a falling tetromino, rotation, movement, and wall-kick rotation logic.
- renderer.js:
  - Renderer class: Draws the board, active piece, ghost piece, and next preview to canvases.
- game.js:
  - Game class: Orchestrates piece spawn, falling, locking, scoring, leveling, and timing. Exposes methods for input actions (move, rotate, drops, pause/reset).
- input.js:
  - Input class: Binds keyboard input to game actions (move, rotate, soft/hard drop, pause).

Features implemented:
- All seven standard tetrominoes (I, O, T, S, Z, J, L).
- Movement, rotation with basic wall kicks, hard drop, soft drop.
- Ghost piece visualization.
- 7-bag randomizer for piece generation.
- Scoring: Singles/Doubles/Triples/Tetris; soft/hard drop points; level multiplier.
- Level increases every 10 lines; drop speed increases with level.
- Game over detection; pause/resume; restart button.
- Board updates after each move or drop.

