"The Pause/Resume key handling conflicts and can break resume: both input.js and main.js listen for KeyP. input.js toggles Game.paused/stopped without restarting the RAF loop, while main.js also toggles via the Pause button click. This can cause a double-toggle (net no change) or leave the game un-resumed because no new RAF is scheduled.

How to fix:
- Centralize KeyP handling in main.js (so it can properly call startLoop on resume) and remove it from input.js.

Edits:
1) input.js — remove KeyP handling and update the docstring.
- Before:
  // in onKeyDown switch
  case 'KeyP':
    e.preventDefault();
    this.game.togglePause();
    break;

  // docstring mentions KeyP
- After:
  // Remove the KeyP case entirely

  // Update docstring to:
  const __DOC__ = `
  Input class attaches keydown/keyup handlers:
  - ArrowLeft/ArrowRight: move
  - ArrowDown: soft drop
  - ArrowUp / KeyX: rotate CW
  - KeyZ: rotate CCW
  - Space: hard drop
  (Pause/Resume via 'P' is handled in main.js to keep UI and loop state in sync.)
  `;

2) main.js — keep the existing KeyP binding, optionally guard to avoid future conflicts:
document.addEventListener('keydown', (e) => {
  if (e.defaultPrevented) return;
  if (e.code === 'KeyP') {
    btnPause.click(); // ensures button label and RAF loop are managed
  } else if (e.code === 'KeyR') {
    btnRestart.click();
  } else if (e.code === 'Enter') {
    btnStart.click();
  }
});

This ensures pressing P pauses/resumes correctly, updates the button text, and restarts the animation loop when resuming."
